Police in Bhisho have appealed to the public for assistance with information that might help them in locating 30-year-old man, Masixole Maji, who went missing from his home in Ngqika Avenue, at Lolo Park, Bhisho, on 17 June 2017. According to the police, he left his home without saying where he was going to and never returned. He was last seen wearing a black jacket, black jean trouser and grey tekkies, said police spokesperson, Captain Siphokazi Mawisa.She added that preliminary investigations were done with no success.Anyone who can shed light on his disappearance can contact Detective Warrant Officer Velile Zola of Bhisho SAPS on 040 608 2626 or 078 075 1088.